From: David Decotigny <decot@google.com>
Date: Wed, 27 Apr 2011 18:32:39 +0000
Subject: ethtool: Use full 32 bit speed range in ethtool's set_settings
References: FATE#311863 ,bnc#699089
Patch-mainline: v3.0-rc1
Git-commit: 25db0338813a8915457636b1f6abe6a28fa73f8d

This makes sure the ethtool's set_settings() callback of network
drivers don't ignore the 16 most significant bits when ethtool calls
their set_settings().

All drivers compiled with make allyesconfig on x86_64 have been
updated.

Signed-off-by: David Decotigny <decot@google.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/igb/igb_ethtool.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/igb/igb_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/igb/igb_ethtool.c
@@ -222,7 +222,8 @@ static int igb_set_settings(struct net_d
 		if (adapter->fc_autoneg)
 			hw->fc.requested_mode = e1000_fc_default;
 	} else {
-		if (igb_set_spd_dplx(adapter, ecmd->speed + ecmd->duplex)) {
+		u32 speed = ethtool_cmd_speed(ecmd);
+		if (igb_set_spd_dplx(adapter, speed + ecmd->duplex)) {
 			clear_bit(__IGB_RESETTING, &adapter->state);
 			return -EINVAL;
 		}
